Key
public static enum Key.Direction
extends Enum<Key.Direction>

Enumeration of possible qualifiers for the traverse and remove methods. Values include EQ, GT, GTEQ, LT and LTEQ.

Enum Constant Summary
EQ
          Indicates for traverse that only the specified key, if it exists, is to be returned.
GT
          Indicates for traverse that the next larger key is to be returned.
GTEQ
          Indicates for traverse that the specified key, if it exists, or else the next larger key is to be returned.
LT
          Indicates for traverse that the next smaller key is to be returned.
LTEQ
          Indicates for traverse that the specified key, if it exists, or else the next smaller key is to be returned.

Enum Constant Detail

EQ

public static final Key.Direction EQ
Indicates for traverse that only the specified key, if it exists, is to be returned. Indicates for remove that only the specified key is to be removed.

LT

public static final Key.Direction LT
Indicates for traverse that the next smaller key is to be returned. Not valid for remove.

LTEQ

public static final Key.Direction LTEQ
Indicates for traverse that the specified key, if it exists, or else the next smaller key is to be returned. Not valid for remove.

GT

public static final Key.Direction GT
Indicates for traverse that the next larger key is to be returned. Indicates for remove that a range of keys following but not including the specified key is to be removed.

GTEQ

public static final Key.Direction GTEQ
Indicates for traverse that the specified key, if it exists, or else the next larger key is to be returned. Indicates for remove that a range of keys including and following the specified key is to be removed.
